-- Repsol, Prisa, Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria, Reyal Urbis: Spanish Preview
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2010-12-29T07:30:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/repsol-promotora-de-informaciones-spanish-stock-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Spanish trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
after company names. Share prices are from the last close.  Spain’s benchmark  IBEX 35 Index  advanced 0.1 percent to
9,903.50 in Madrid.  Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA  (BBVA SM): Inveravante, the
investment firm of Spanish billionaire Manuel Jove, boosted its
stake in BBVA to 5.067 percent, after the last share sale that
Spain’s second biggest lender carried out, Expansion reported,
without citing anyone. The stock fell 0.3 percent to 7.61 euros.  Promotora de Informaciones SA  (PRS SM): Digital Plus, a
company in which Prisa’s television unit has a 56 percent stake,
sold a building in Madrid to Flagland Spain SL, the investment
arm of the fund W.P. Carey & Co. LLC for 80 million euros ($105
million), Prisa said. The stock lost 0.3 percent to 1.55 euros.  Repsol YPF SA  (REP SM): China Petroleum & Chemical Corp.
completed its $7.11 billion purchase of a 40 percent stake in
Repsol’s Brazilian unit, as the Spanish oil company raised funds
to develop offshore projects. Repsol shares rose 0.2 percent to
20.79 euros.  Reyal Urbis SA  (REY SM): Spain’s biggest real-estate
company sold the Tryp Ambassador hotel in Madrid to Caixa
Renting, a unit of La Caixa, for 23 million euros, Cinco Dias
reported, citing Reyal Urbis. The sale is part of a debt-
restructuring plan between Madrid-based Reyal and lenders and
will provide Reyal with a net gain of 18.7 million euros, the
newspaper said. The shares climbed 2.1 percent to 98 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
